article.linkText: Wolf's 19 lead Yale past Cornell in Ivy League Tournament 69-57
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Danny Wolf scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and second-seeded Yale beat Cornell 69-57 victory in the Ivy League Tournament on Saturday. Yale will face No. 4-seed Brown in the championship game on Sunday. Brown stunned top-seed Princeton also on Saturday. August Mahoney scored 12 of his 16 points before halftime and was 5-for-9 shooting from beyond the arc. Matt Knowling had 12 points and finished 6 of 10 from the floor for the Bulldogs (21-9). Jake Fiegen and Chris Manon each scored 10 points for the Big Red (22-7). Yale took the lead with 18:10 remaining in the first half and never looked back. The Bulldogs led 37-25 at halftime. Yale extended its lead to 44-25 during the second half, fueled by a 7-0 scoring run. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
